claim.claim-text:
1. A braided stent, for implanting in a patient's vessel, comprising:
a plurality of braided strands having an average strand thickness, the plurality of braided strands forming pores in open areas between strands, the open areas defining an open surface area;
wherein the plurality of braided strands comprises a first plurality of strands consisting of a first metallic material and a second plurality of strands, consisting of a second metallic material, different from the first material, wherein each of the first plurality of strands has a first width and each of the second plurality of strands has a second width, different than the first width;
wherein the first material comprises platinum;
wherein the stent is self-expandable from a radially compressed configuration to a first radially expanded configuration and is adjustable from the first radially expanded configuration to a second radially expanded configuration in response to an axially compressive force;
wherein the pores have an average pore length along a length of the stent;
wherein the stent has a total porosity equal to a ratio of the open surface area of the stent to a total surface area of the stent;
wherein a first portion of the braided stent, when in the first expanded configuration, is configured to adjust, in response to the axially compressive force, to the second expanded configuration, such that the first portion of the stent (i) reduces in length from a first length to a second length, (ii) reduces in porosity from a first porosity to a second porosity, and (iii) maintains a substantially equal lumenal cross-sectional dimension as in the first expanded configuration; and
wherein, when the stent is in the first expanded configuration, the total porosity of the stent multiplied by the average pore length is between about 0.10 and about 0.85 mm.

15. A braided stent, for implanting in a patient's vessel, comprising:
a plurality of braided strands having an average strand thickness, the plurality of braided strands forming pores in open areas between strands, the open areas defining an open surface area;
wherein the plurality of braided strands comprises a first plurality of strands consisting of a first metallic material and a second plurality of strands, consisting of a second metallic material, different from the first material, wherein each of the first plurality of strands has a first width and each of the second plurality of strands has a second width, different than the first width;
wherein the first material comprises platinum;
wherein a first portion and a second portion of the stent are self-expandable from a radially compressed configuration to a first radially expanded configuration and the first portion is adjustable from the first radially expanded configuration to a second radially expanded configuration in response to an axially compressive force applied thereto;
wherein the pores have an average pore length along a length of the stent;
wherein the stent has a total porosity equal to a ratio of the open surface area of the stent to a total surface area of the stent;
wherein the first portion of the braided stent, when in the first expanded configuration, is configured to adjust, in response to the axially compressive force, to the second expanded configuration, such that the first portion of the stent (i) reduces in length from a first length to a second length, (ii) decreases in porosity from a first porosity to a second porosity, and (iii) maintains a substantially equal lumenal cross-sectional dimension as in the first expanded configuration;
wherein the second porosity of the first portion, while in the second expanded configuration, is less than a porosity of the second portion while in the first expanded configuration; and
wherein, when the stent is in the first expanded configuration, the total porosity of the stent multiplied by the average strand thickness is between about 0.0007 and about 0.0014 inches.

27. A stent, comprising:
a plurality of braided strands forming pores in open areas between strands, the open areas defining an open surface area, the stent having a total porosity defined by a ratio of the open surface area of the stent to a total surface area of the stent;
wherein the plurality of braided strands comprises a first plurality of strands consisting of a first metallic material and a second plurality of strands, consisting of a second metallic material, different from the first material, wherein each of the first plurality of strands has a first width and each of the second plurality of strands has a second width, different than the first width;
wherein the first material comprises platinum;
wherein the stent is self-expandable from a radially compressed configuration to a first radially expanded configuration; and
wherein at least a portion of the stent, when in the first radially expanded configuration, is configured to adjust, in response to an axially compressive force, to a second radially expanded configuration, such that the at least a portion of the stent (i) reduces in length from a first length to a second length, (ii) reduces in porosity from a first porosity to a second porosity, and (iii) maintains a substantially equal lumenal cross-sectional dimension as in the first radially expanded configuration.

38. A braided stent, for implanting in a patient's vessel, comprising:
a plurality of braided strands forming pores in open areas between strands, the strands having an outer surface area, the outer surface area and open areas defining a total surface area of the stent, a ratio of the outer surface area to the total surface area defining a stent lattice density;
wherein the plurality of braided strands comprises a first plurality of strands consisting of a first metallic material and a second plurality of strands, consisting of a second metallic material, different from the first material, wherein each of the first plurality of strands has a first width and each of the second plurality of strands has a second width, different than the first width;
wherein the first material comprises platinum;
wherein a first portion and a second portion of the stent are self-expandable from a radially compressed configuration to a first radially expanded configuration, and the first portion is adjustable from the first radially expanded configuration to a second radially expanded configuration in response to an axially compressive force applied to the first portion while the second portion remains in the first expanded configuration;
wherein, when in the first expanded configuration, the first portion and the second portion have substantially equal porosity and lumenal cross-sectional dimension; and
wherein the first portion of the braided stent, when in the first expanded configuration, is configured to adjust, in response to the axially compressive force, to the second expanded configuration, such that the first portion of the stent (i) reduces in length from a first length to a second length, (ii) increases in lattice density from a first lattice density to a second lattice density, and (iii) maintains a substantially equal lumenal cross-sectional dimension as in the first expanded configuration.
